me mandatory for App Store submissions in Spring 2024. This skill covers the manifest file format, required reason APIs, tracking declarations, third-party SDK privacy, and App Tracking Transparency.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:14:- Asks about \"privacy manifest\" or \"PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy\"\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:15:- Mentions \"required reason API\" or App Store privacy rejection\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:16:- Needs to declare \"tracking domains\" or \"NSPrivacyTracking\"\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:17:- Asks about \"App Tracking Transparency\" or ATT\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:18:- Wants to audit third-party SDK privacy declarations\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:19:- Is preparing an app for App Store submission and mentions privacy\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:20:- Gets an App Store Connect warning about missing privacy manifests\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:21:- Asks about \"privacy nutrition labels\" or App Store privacy details\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:27:| Creating PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy from scratch | Privacy Manifest File Format + Required Reason APIs |\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:29:| Declaring tracking domains | Tracking Domains and NSPrivacyTracking |\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:30:| Third-party SDK privacy | Third-Party SDK Declarations |\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:31:| Implementing ATT | App Tracking Transparency |\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:32:| Filling out App Store privacy labels | Privacy Nutrition Labels |\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:40:Glob: **/PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:41:Grep: \"NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes|NSPrivacyTracking|NSPrivacyTrackingDomains\"\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:47:Grep: \"ATTrackingManager|requestTrackingAuthorization\"\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:52:Check: Does PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy exist? Are all required reason APIs declared? Is NSPrivacyTracking correct? Are tracking domains listed? Do third-party SDKs have their own manifests? Use the sections below to generate correct entries.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:58:The privacy manifest is a property list named `PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy`. Add it via File > New > File > App Privacy in Xcode. Four required top-level keys:\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:66:    <key>NSPrivacyTracking</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:68:    <key>NSPrivacyTrackingDomains</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:70:    <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:72:    <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:80:- **App targets**: Add PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy to the root of the app bundle. In Xcode, ensure it is included in the target's \"Copy Bundle Resources\" build phase.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:81:- **Frameworks/SDKs**: Place PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy in the root of the framework bundle.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:82:- **Swift packages**: Place PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy in the package's resource bundle and declare it in Package.swift:\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:89:        .copy(\"PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy\")\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:100:### File Timestamp APIs (NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryFileTimestamp)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:113:### System Boot Time APIs (NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategorySystemBootTime)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:125:### Disk Space APIs (NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryDiskSpace)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:138:### User Defaults APIs (NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryUserDefaults)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:151:### Active Keyboards API (NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryActiveKeyboards)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:168:## Tracking Domains and NSPrivacyTracking\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:170:`NSPrivacyTracking` declares whether your app tracks users. Apple defines tracking as: linking user/device data from your app with data from other companies' apps, websites, or offline properties for advertising, or sharing data with data brokers.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:172:Apple does **not** consider these to be tracking: on-device-only data linking, fraud detection, security, or compliance.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:174:If NSPrivacyTracking is true:\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:175:- You must implement App Tracking Transparency (ATT) before any tracking occurs\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:176:- List all tracking domains in `NSPrivacyTrackingDomains` (the system blocks them until ATT is granted)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:179:<key>NSPrivacyTracking</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:181:<key>NSPrivacyTrackingDomains</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:188:If your app does not track users, set NSPrivacyTracking to false and leave the domains array empty.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:196:Starting Spring 2024, apps that include commonly used third-party SDKs must ensure those SDKs provide their own PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy files. Apple publishes a list of SDKs that require privacy manifests and signatures, including Alamofire, FBSDKCoreKit, Firebase, Google Analytics, Kingfisher, Lottie, Realm, SDWebImage, and many others. See [Apple's full list](https://developer.apple.com/support/third-party-SDK-requirements/).\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:205:Glob: **/Pods/**/PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:206:Glob: **/.build/**/PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:207:Glob: **/Carthage/**/PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:211:If a third-party SDK lacks a privacy manifest and uses required reason APIs, contact the SDK maintainer. As a temporary workaround, declare the SDK's API usage in your app's manifest, but this is not a long-term solution.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:217:### When ATT Is Required\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:219:You must present the ATT prompt if:\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:220:- NSPrivacyTracking is true in your privacy manifest\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:222:- You use advertising identifiers (IDFA) for tracking purposes\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:224:You do not need ATT for:\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:226:- SKAdNetwork attribution (privacy-preserving, no user-level data)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:234:import AppTrackingTransparency\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:237:    ATTrackingManager.requestTrackingAuthorization { status in\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:257:<key>NSUserTrackingUsageDescription</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:263:SKAdNetwork provides privacy-preserving install attribution without user-level data. It does not require ATT permission. Register ad network identifiers in Info.plist:\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:279:The privacy manifest feeds into the App Store privacy labels (\"nutrition labels\") displayed on your app's product page. The connection works as follows:\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:283:| NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes | \"Data Used to Track You\" and \"Data Linked to You\" sections |\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:284:| NSPrivacyTracking | Determines if \"Data Used to Track You\" section appears |\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:285:| NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes | Not directly shown, but required for submission |\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:287:### NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes Format\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:289:Each entry declares: data type, whether it is linked to user identity, whether it is used for tracking, and purposes.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:292:<key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:295:        <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataType</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:296:        <string>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypeEmailAddress</string>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:297:        <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypeLinked</key>  <!-- linked to user identity? -->\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:299:        <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypeTracking</key>  <!-- used for tracking? -->\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:301:        <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypePurposes</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:303:            <string>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypePurposeAppFunctionality</string>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:309:Common data types: `EmailAddress`, `Name`, `PhoneNumber`, `Location`, `DeviceID`, `CrashData`, `PerformanceData`, `ProductInteraction`, `PurchaseHistory` (prefix each with `NSPrivacyCollectedDataType`).\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:311:Common purposes: `AppFunctionality`, `Analytics`, `ThirdPartyAdvertising`, `ProductPersonalization` (prefix each with `NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypePurpose`).\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:313:The App Store privacy label must match your manifest declarations. Inconsistencies trigger review delays or rejections.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:319:Generate a consolidated report via Product > Generate Privacy Report (or from the Organizer after archiving). Xcode produces a PDF listing all privacy manifest entries from the app and every embedded framework/SDK. Use this to verify all required reason APIs are declared, confirm third-party SDKs include their own manifests, and cross-check collected data types before filling out App Store Connect privacy labels.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:325:1. **Missing PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy entirely** -- Every App Store submission requires a privacy manifest. Without one, expect a warning or rejection.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:327:2. **Using UserDefaults without declaring it** -- Almost every app uses UserDefaults. Declare `NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryUserDefaults` with reason `CA92.1`.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:335:5. **NSPrivacyTracking true without ATT** -- If you declare tracking, you must implement the ATT prompt before any tracking occurs. Missing this causes rejection.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:337:6. **Stale privacy nutrition labels** -- After updating your manifest, also update the App Store Connect privacy labels. Inconsistencies trigger review issues.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:343:- [ ] PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy exists in the app target's bundle resources\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:344:- [ ] NSPrivacyTracking set correctly (true only if the app tracks users)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:345:- [ ] NSPrivacyTrackingDomains lists all tracking domains (if tracking is true)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:348:- [ ] NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes lists all collected data\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:349:- [ ] Third-party SDKs include their own PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy and are signed\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:350:- [ ] ATT prompt implemented if NSPrivacyTracking is true\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:351:- [ ] NSUserTrackingUsageDescription in Info.plist if ATT is used\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:352:- [ ] App Store Connect privacy labels match manifest declarations\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:353:- [ ] Xcode privacy report generated and reviewed (Product > Generate Privacy Report)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:354:- [ ] Swift packages declare PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy in their resource bundle\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:360:Most apps need at minimum UserDefaults declared. Start from the minimal manifest structure above and populate `NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes`:\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:363:<key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:366:        <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:367:        <string>NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryUserDefaults</string>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:368:        <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypeReasons</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:374:        <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:375:        <string>NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryFileTimestamp</string>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:376:        <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypeReasons</key>\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:386:Add to the template above: set `NSPrivacyTracking` to `true`, list tracking domains, add `NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes` entries (see \"Privacy Nutrition Labels\" for format), implement ATT, and add `NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryDiskSpace` with reason `7D9E.1` if sending disk metrics off-device.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:392:- [Apple: Privacy manifest files](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/bundleresources/privacy_manifest_files)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:393:- [Apple: Describing use of required reason API](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/bundleresources/privacy_manifest_files/describing_use_of_required_reason_api)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:395:- [Apple: App Tracking Transparency](https://developer.apple.com/documentation/apptrackingtransparency)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/privacy-manifests/SKILL.md:397:- [Apple: App privacy details on the App Store](https://developer.apple.com/app-store/app-privacy-details/)\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/platform-specifics.md:273:let healthStore = HKHealthStore()\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/platform-specifics.md:280:healthStore.requestAuthorization(toShare: nil, read: readTypes) { success, error in\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/platform-specifics.md:284:// Never log health data\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/platform-specifics.md:286:// Always explain why health data is needed\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:71:- [OneSignal.md](integrations/OneSignal.md) - Push notifications (optional)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:471:- **`@Published`, `@ObservedObject`, `@StateObject`.** These property wrappers are dead in this codebase. Use `@State` with `@Observable` types and let SwiftUI do the tracking.\napps/waketask-iphone/.agents/skills/security/SKILL.md:38:- Sensitive data types (credentials, health data, financial, PII)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1151:**What you're doing:** Customizing the privacy policy template with your app details.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1155:**File:** `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Resources/privacy.md`\napps/waketask-ip