{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_24","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"mkdir -p .workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews && cat > .workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/implementation-security.md <<'EOF'\n# Implementation Security Review — WakeTask iPhone\n\nDate: 2026-05-14\nScope: app code, configs, scripts, CI workflows, legal/privacy artifacts present in \"'`apps/waketask-iphone`\n\n## Verdict\nVERDICT: REJECTED\n\nBlocking issues are present in security/privacy/legal handling.\n\n## Blocking Findings\n\n### 1) In-app legal/privacy text is placeholder boilerplate and does not match customized policy docs\nSeverity: BLOCKING (Privacy/Legal)\n\nEvidence:\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/FeatureSettings/Sources/FeatureSettings/Views/LegalDocumentView.swift`\n  - Contains placeholders like `Last Updated: [DATE]` and `[CONTACT EMAIL]`\n  - Generic policy text, not WakeTask-specific terms/privacy/subscription terms\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/LegalDocumentView.swift`\n  - Same placeholder/generic legal content\n- Customized docs exist but are not what UI legal views render:\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Resources/privacy.md`\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Resources/terms.md`\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Resources/subscription_terms.md`\n\nWhy blocking:\n- User-facing legal disclosures are materially inconsistent with shipped behavior/policies and contain placeholder values.\n- This is a release blocker for privacy/legal compliance and App Store submission readiness.\n\nRequired fix:\n- Replace both `LegalDocumentView.swift` implementations with runtime loading/rendering of the maintained legal resources, or fully sync embedded legal text with production policy content and real contact/date values.\n\n---\n\n### 2) PII/user-content is logged in plaintext in multiple paths\nSeverity: BLOCKING (Privacy)\n\nEvidence:\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/FeatureChat/Sources/FeatureChat/ViewModels/ChatViewModel.swift`\n  - `AppLogger.info(\"Handling reply from notification: '\"\\\\(replyText)\\\", ...)\"'` logs notification reply body (user text)\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Storage/Sources/Storage/Repositories/MemoryRepository.swift`\n  - `AppLogger.debug(\"Deleted conflicting memory: '\"\\\\(memory.content)\\\", ...)\"'` logs full memory content\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Storage/Sources/Storage/Services/MemoryRetriever.swift`\n  - `AppLogger.debug(\"Extracted keywords for memory search: '\"\\\\(keywords)\\\", ...)\"'` logs user-prompt-derived terms\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Core/Sources/Core/AppLogger.swift`\n  - Logging calls do **not** auto-redact; redaction is opt-in per call-site.\n\nWhy blocking:\n- User-generated text and derived semantic content can include personal/sensitive data and is persisted in OSLog/diagnostic streams.\n- Violates least-data logging principles and can conflict with declared privacy posture.\n\nRequired fix:\n- Remove content-bearing logs or redact aggressively at call-sites (`AppLogger.redacted(...)`) for any user-provided or user-derived text.\n- Prefer metadata-only logs (counts/IDs/status) over content logs.\n\n---\n\n### 3) Privacy manifest appears incomplete relative to implemented data flows and SDK usage\nSeverity: BLOCKING (Privacy/App Store)\n\nEvidence:\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy`\n  - `NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes` is empty\n  - Only `UserDefaults` required-reason API is declared\n- App includes flows likely involving user identifiers/account/subscription/diagnostics/push:\n  - Auth/session (`CompositionRoot`, `Auth` integration)\n  - RevenueCat (`CompositionRoot` payments wiring)\n  - Optional Crashlytics and OneSignal integration hooks (`CompositionRoot`, `AppDelegate`)\n\nWhy blocking:\n- Current manifest/disclosure posture is not clearly aligned with actual app behavior and enabled SDK paths.\n- Raises App Store privacy compliance risk.\n\nRequired fix:\n- Perform a full privacy data inventory and align `PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy` + App Store privacy answers with real runtime data collection and enabled integrations.\n- Ensure optional integrations are either gated/documented consistently or removed from shipped target when unused.\n\n## Non-Blocking Observations\n\n1) No hardcoded production secrets were found in reviewed app source/config files; generated config uses placeholders (`Generated/Configuration.swift`, `Config/Secrets.example.xcconfig`).\n2) Secret scanning is wired into CI scripts:\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh`\n- `apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/ci/run-foundation-gates.sh`\n\nBut regex coverage is basic; consider adding a dedicated scanner (e.g., gitleaks) as defense-in-depth.\n\n3) CI/scripts avoid printing secret values and only report presence flags in quality script.\n4) Auth/payment/AI integration paths use boilerplate abstractions/composition (`AuthClient`, `PaymentsClient`, `LLMClient` via `CompositionRoot`).\n\n## Notes on Requested Artifact Inputs\n\nThe expected workflow artifact directory `.workflow/iphone-app-factory` (spec/architecture/phase-evidence outputs) was not present in this workspace at review time. Review was completed against the app repository contents and generated files available under `apps/waketask-iphone`.\n\n## Release Gate Decision\n\nStatus: BLOCKED\n\nMust fix all blocking findings before simplification/release hardening proceeds.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
